        stuff(); 
        return this;
    )
</code></pre>
This aMethod returns an A when invoked on an A instance or a B, B extends A, if is a B instance. Handy for builders and fluid apis:<p><pre><code>    B thisIsB = new B();
    thisIsB.aMethod().bMethod();</code></pre>
